This old church was used during the 16th to 17th centuries.
There is a nave, chancel arch and gable with a double-arched bell-turret still remaining. Kinsaley means “head of the brine” which is a reminder at one time the sea came to the parish borders. If you look closely you can see the remnants of sea shells in the grounds.
